The driver of the car that crashed into the women was released from hospital at 2.45am on Monday.

He was  charged with three counts of dangerous driving occasioning grievous bodily harm, one count of drive furiously occasioning actual bodily harm and negligent driving occasioning grievous bodily harm.

He has been refused bail and is scheduled to appear in Newtown Local Court on Monday.

